Blind							KEY:Blind ~ Yrthak						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Weakness.Extraordinary				DESC:A yrthak sees and senses exclusively through its blindsight ability, which is based on sound and movement - beyond 120 feet, it is considered blind.  A deaf yrthak is effectively blinded as well except against adjacent foes - its weak eyesight functions enough for it to attack targets this close, although in such cases these creatures still gain the benefit of concealment (20%% miss chance) because of the creature's poor vision.  It is invulnerable to all sight-based effects and attacks, including gaze attacks.	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Immunity to Gaze Attacks ~ Yrthak|Immunity to Sight-Based Attacks ~ Yrthak|Immunity to Visual Effects and Illusions ~ Yrthak	SOURCEPAGE:p.289

Immunity to Gaze Attacks			KEY:Immunity to Gaze Attacks ~ Yrthak			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Immunity	DESC:You are never subject to gaze attacks.																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.290	ASPECT:Immunity|Gaze Attacks

Immunity to Visual Effects and Illusions	KEY:Immunity to Visual Effects and Illusions ~ Yrthak	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Immunity	DESC:You are never subject to visual effects and illusions.																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.290	ASPECT:Immunity|Visual Effects and Illusions

Immunity to Sight-Based Attacks		KEY:Immunity to Sight-Based Attacks ~ Yrthak		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Immunity	DESC:You are never subject to sight-based attacks.																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.290	ASPECT:Immunity|Sight-Based Attacks

Explosion						KEY:Explosion ~ Yrthak						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary			DESC:As a standard action, a yrthak can fire its sonic lance at the ground, a large rock, a stone wall, or a similar nonmagical object within 60 feet to create an explosion.  This attack deals 2d6 points of piercing damage to all within 10 feet of the effect's center.																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.289

Sonic Lance						KEY:Sonic Lance ~ Yrthak					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary					DESC:Once per round, a yrthak can focus sonic energy in a 60-foot ray that deals 8d6 sonic damage to one target.

